The approach is to use two pointers: i and k

class Solution {
    public int removeElement(int[] nums, int val) {
        int k=0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[i]!=val){
                nums[k]=nums[i];
                k++;
            }
        }
        return k;
    }
}

Moreover we can reduce to one pointer by going from backwards

for(int i=0;i<n;){
if(nums[i]==val){
nums[i]=nums[n-1];
n--;
}
else{
i++;
}
}
return n;
}}
